===English===
==Etymology==
From the Greek ''psalterion'' ''(ψαληρου)'': a stringed instrument, through Latin ''psaltarium'': stringed instrument of the lute kind; through French ''sautier; psaltier''; to Old English ''sauter; psauter''.
===Noun===
1 The Book of Psalms. Often applied to a book containing the Psalms seperately printed.

2 Specifically for [[Anglican]]s, the Book of Common Prayer which contains the Book of Psalms. For [[Catholic]]s, the [[Breviary]] containing the Psalms arranged for each day of the week.

3 In the Roman Catholic Church, A [[rosary]] consisting of one hundred and fifty beads, corresponding to the number of the Psalms.